author: CJ Andrea Molo

text: Oh, and btw, if you didn't know, THE HUNGER GAMES movie was PG13. The director himself said that they wanted to make sure that they kept the depth and meaning of the movie even though there wasn't any blood or gore. Did you just say, didn't show people dying? EXCUSE ME, BUT IT DID. -sigh- I understand why people may think that THE HUNGER GAMES, and Battle Royale seem so similar because I've read and watched both. So I know my stuff. I'm not saying that Battle Royale is bad,because it was awesome
author: CJ Andrea Molo

text: But in THE HUNGER GAMES, they didn't have necklaces to blow them up and they didn't have a time limit. In Battle Royale, it was more of a secretive thing from public. In THE HUNGER GAMES, it was an annual thing that the WORLD had to participate in, so everyone knew abou it.
author: CJ Andrea Molo

text: Also, in Battle Royale, did they start a rebellion to bring down the government? Was the girl strong and independent? Were they able to have freedom? NO. They had to run away in hiding in Battle Royale, the girl was meek, fearful, and depending, and they had no amount of freedom at the end. They were outlaws. THE HUNGER GAMES is different to Battle Royale in many different ways, and don't you say that I don't know anything, because I read and watched both. So hun, I know what I'm talking about.
author: CJ Andrea Molo

text: Just re-watched after thinking about this trailer. One of the best trailers of all time honestly. The way the sound and visuals came together on this movie, I swear every crew member read this book (like the world) and really made it come to life. remembering how much the books affected me and then when the trailer came out (I still know every word to it from watching it so much) and it being so perfect down to sounding exactly how I imagined every scene in the book to sound like is indescribable. Yes, the other movies are amazing but nothing will ever top the feeling of when the first trailer came out. I shed a tear or two every time "I volunteer as tribute!" just by the mask scale of feelings to how much it means to me and the world. Also, this movie just gives you an eerie feeling unlike any other, I believe.

I guess jealousy took over and in my frustration, I said Damn it, so I won't be getting laid?!?! A lady next to me reached for my hand and said "I volunteer as tribute". I couldn't stop laughing.  My friend hooked up with someone and I went home alone, but laughed about it the whole way.
